Miami Herald, July 5, 1987

Alfonso Chardy Reagan Aides and the Secret Government NATIONAL CRISIS PLAN From 1982 to 1984, [Oliver] North assisted FEMA, the U.S. government’s chief national crisis-management unit, in revising contingency plans for dealing with nuclear war, insurrection or massive military mobilization. North’s involvement with FEMA set off the first major clash between the official government and the advisers
